        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 4:12PM MST by NWS Phoenix AZ</headline>
        <description>At 411 PM MST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Goldfield Ranch, or near Sugarloaf Mountain, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sugarloaf Mountain, Saguaro Lake, Salt River Tubing Recreation Area,
and Goldfield Ranch.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
